      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I guess I just couldn't help myself – goblins are always lurking in the shadows, waiting to pounce on unsuspecting buyers! But, I promise, I'll get back to the banking part.\n\nIn the escrow account, the money is typically managed by a third-party escrow agent, such as a title company or a specialized escrow service. These agents are usually independent of the realtor or the seller, and their role is to hold the funds until the conditions are met.\n\nThink of the escrow agent as a neutral, impartial \"goblin wrangler\" – someone who keeps the funds safe and ensures that everything runs smoothly. They're usually responsible for collecting and disbursing the funds, as well as monitoring the account to ensure that all payments are made on time.\n\nIn Toronto, the escrow agent is usually a separate entity from the realtor, and they may work with the title company or a specialized escrow service to manage the account. The realtor's role is more focused on facilitating the transaction and ensuring that all parties are aware of the escrow account and its requirements.\n\nAs for the realtor's involvement, they might be responsible for setting up the escrow account, but they wouldn't typically be the",
